You will be part of the Product team in charge of planning the linehaul of our postal mails shipment, monitoring the movement to ensure smooth delivery, as well as developing new routes for any new business projects.

Responsibilities:

  Drive service delivery to our customer by maintaining monthly and quarterly performance reports to monitor and analyse airlines transit time performance
  Perform claims on suppliers where there is failure of service level agreement
  Manage Cost Database by updating all airlines and vendors buying rates as procured by the respective Managers
  Monitor and analyse internal transhipment leadtime performance
  Provide support to Product Team on liaison and coordination with vendors
  Provide support on airlines’ and vendors’ invoice checking.


Requirements:

  At least 1 year of working experience in airfreight and related field preferred.
  Possess at least Professional Certificate/Nitec, preferably in Logistic/Supply Chain Management or equivalent.
  Highly Proficient in MS Office, especially MS Excel.
  Strong analytical and data driven mindset.
  Good understanding of Sales/Operations (frontline experience).
  Experience working with teams across geographies preferred.
  Ability to prioritise, work under pressure, and action-oriented.
  Willing to work on weekends.
  Candidates who can communicate in both English and Chinese preferred (to liaise with our English and Chinese speaking customers and associates).
